					staminal column 0.5(-1) mm long, synandrium 0.5(-1) mm diam., anthers subglobose, sessile or short-stalked, c. 0.2 mm diameter.

Female flowers:
					pedicel 2-4 mm long, subapically articulate;
					perianth 2-4 mm diam.;
					ovary subglobose, c. 1 mm diam., glabrous or sparsely hairy;
					styles (2 or) 3, with stigma each 0.5-1 mm long.

Flowers large, puberulous;
					corolla rotate;
					petals free, white, long-fringed, the in bud exposed portion conspicuously veined.

Male flowers:
